Jira User Story (Revised for Source System Alignment)
Title: EIM: Add "EIM-" Prefix to Issue IDs to Match Source System
User Story:
As a user, I want all Issue IDs within the "Enterprise Issue Management" (EIM) module to be prefixed with "EIM-", so that the IDs in our application are consistent with the format used in the source system.
Problem Statement:
The "Enterprise Issue Management" (EIM) module displays data from an external source system where the issue identifiers are already formatted with an "EIM-" prefix (e.g., EIM-12345).
Our application currently strips this prefix and displays the ID as a simple number (e.g., 12345). This discrepancy creates significant friction for users who work in both systems. It makes cross-referencing issues difficult, complicates communication when referencing an ID, and can lead to errors when trying to find the corresponding record in the source system.
To eliminate this confusion and create a seamless experience, our application must display the Issue ID in the exact same format as the source system.
Acceptance Criteria (Checklist Style):
 * The Issue ID format in our application must exactly match the format in the source system.
 * The "EIM-" prefix is displayed for every Issue ID within the Enterprise Issue Management module.
 * The new EIM-[IssueID] format is shown consistently across all user views, including:
   * Detail views (e.g., page titles, header fields)
   * List/table views
   * Search results
   * Any data exports (e.g., CSV, PDF)
 * The core numeric part of the ID remains the same. For example, an issue that appears as 12345 should now appear as EIM-12345.
 * Users must be able to successfully search for an issue using both the full prefixed ID (EIM-12345) and the numeric part only (12345).
 * Hyperlinks to issues created before this change should still resolve correctly.
Key Improvements in This Version:
 * Source of Truth is Central: The entire story—from the title to the problem statement—now revolves around the most important driver: matching the source system.
 * Stronger Justification: The problem is no longer just about potential internal confusion. It's about a direct, daily operational conflict (makes cross-referencing difficult) with another critical system. This is a much higher-priority issue.
 * Clearer End Goal: The first acceptance criterion is now a simple, powerful statement: "The Issue ID format in our application must exactly match the format in the source system." This serves as the ultimate definition of success for the development team.
